SIMPLE: metalline
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metalline
<hw>Met"al*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧tallin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Pertaining to, or resembling, a metal; metallic; <as>as,
<ex>metalline</ex> properties</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Impregnated
with metallic salts; chalybeate; <as>as, <ex>metalline</ex>
water</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metalline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Metalline
<hw>Met"al*line</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance of variable composition, but
resembling a soft, dark-colored metal, used in the bearings of machines
for obviating friction, and as a substitute for lubricants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metallist</ent>⟦br⟧
